WEBVTT

00:00.167 --> 00:00.997
- [grunts]
[bell tolls]

00:02.336 --> 00:03.996
- You saved us back there.
You’re basically my hero.

00:04.087 --> 00:06.207
- You’re responsible for
killing Jake’s whole family.

00:06.298 --> 00:08.508
But for some reason, he doesn’t
seem to care about any of that.

00:08.592 --> 00:09.932
- That wasn’t his fault.

00:10.010 --> 00:11.300
Look, I know you’re good.

00:11.386 --> 00:14.806
- What if there’s still
the evil inside me too?

00:14.890 --> 00:17.140
- Look, I have an idea.
We’re gonna need some help.

00:17.226 --> 00:20.436
- I have one last
birthday present for you.

00:20.521 --> 00:22.651
- What about Glenda?
- It’s for them too.

00:22.731 --> 00:24.271
- Meg, look out!
- [screams]

00:24.358 --> 00:28.068
[both screaming]

00:29.446 --> 00:30.906
- I baptize you in the name

00:30.989 --> 00:31.949
of the Father,

00:32.032 --> 00:33.242
the Son,

00:33.325 --> 00:34.625
and the Holy Spirit.

00:34.701 --> 00:36.201
- Amen.
- You’re clean now.

00:36.286 --> 00:38.326
No more evil.

00:38.413 --> 00:40.923
- Sister Ruth,
get rid of that abomination.

00:40.999 --> 00:42.879
- Yes, Father.

00:42.960 --> 00:44.170
[eerie music]

00:44.253 --> 00:47.013
- Holy shit.
- Oh, my God.

00:47.089 --> 00:48.169
- Andy.

00:48.257 --> 00:49.627
[banging]

00:49.716 --> 00:51.926
- What the name of heaven?

00:52.010 --> 00:53.680
[screams]

00:53.762 --> 00:55.682
[dramatic music]

00:55.764 --> 00:58.184
- Does that guy
look familiar?

00:58.267 --> 00:59.807
Andy.

00:59.893 --> 01:00.853
Get him!

01:00.936 --> 01:02.396
[tires squeal]

01:02.479 --> 01:03.399
- This is for Kyle!

01:03.480 --> 01:07.230
♪ ♪

01:07.317 --> 01:10.197
[all screaming]

01:12.281 --> 01:14.241
[explosion booms]

01:14.324 --> 01:18.414
♪ ♪

01:18.495 --> 01:21.365
[Chuckys grunting]

01:27.129 --> 01:28.549
- [growls]

01:28.630 --> 01:33.720
♪ ♪

01:33.802 --> 01:35.302
All right, move him out.

01:35.387 --> 01:37.467
- Let’s go, loser!

01:37.556 --> 01:39.216
[both grunting]

01:39.308 --> 01:41.598
- Bye, Andy.

01:43.937 --> 01:46.937
[explosion]

01:47.024 --> 01:49.904
[Chuckys screaming[

01:56.199 --> 01:59.119
[eerie music]

01:59.202 --> 02:02.962
♪ ♪

02:03.040 --> 02:06.750
- Another pound of flesh.

02:06.835 --> 02:08.085
- [muffled whimpering]

02:08.170 --> 02:11.050
- Don’t mind if I do.

02:11.131 --> 02:13.931
- What happens
when there’s nothing left?

02:14.009 --> 02:16.719
- Then I will cut deeper.

02:16.803 --> 02:19.813
- [muffled whimpering]

02:21.642 --> 02:24.642
[muffled groaning]

02:26.480 --> 02:30.190
- They’ve been torturing him
for a year.

02:30.275 --> 02:32.685
- Tiffany has let
Chucky Prime escape.

02:32.778 --> 02:34.358
They’re on their way here now.

02:34.446 --> 02:37.276
- "Chucky Prime"?

02:37.366 --> 02:39.486
That’s absurd.

02:39.576 --> 02:42.406
- [whimpering]

02:42.496 --> 02:44.616
- He was the first.

02:44.706 --> 02:46.036
- [gasps]

02:47.209 --> 02:48.999
- Then he got sloppy.

02:49.086 --> 02:53.876
First, he gets trapped
inside of Nica Pierce.

02:53.965 --> 02:58.425
Then he lets Tiffany
chew him up and spit him out.

02:58.512 --> 03:00.142
There’s nothing prime
about him.

03:00.222 --> 03:01.972
He’s low-grade meat.

03:02.057 --> 03:04.597
All fat.

03:04.685 --> 03:05.855
Sorry, Andy.

03:07.771 --> 03:10.691
That’s a rather tender subject
for you, isn’t it?

03:10.774 --> 03:13.614
- [groaning]

03:13.694 --> 03:15.154
- [gasps]

03:15.237 --> 03:21.947
♪ ♪

03:23.078 --> 03:26.868
- So what happened to Tiffany?

03:26.957 --> 03:30.627
- Your infatuation with that
woman has always mystified me.

03:30.711 --> 03:34.671
- I am merely infatuated

03:34.756 --> 03:36.836
with the thought

03:36.925 --> 03:39.005
of her demise.

03:39.094 --> 03:40.804
- That lady always
freaked me out.

03:40.887 --> 03:43.137
- What about my men?
- Seriously.

03:43.223 --> 03:44.313
My mom should get
her money back

03:44.391 --> 03:45.641
for all those therapy sessions.

03:45.726 --> 03:48.646
- Your brawny assassin is dead,

03:48.729 --> 03:50.859
and the scout is
unaccounted for.

03:50.939 --> 03:52.689
- And those kids
are still breathing.

03:54.276 --> 03:56.146
- Let me do it.

03:56.236 --> 03:59.026
Let me kill them for you.

03:59.114 --> 04:00.914
- No.

04:00.991 --> 04:05.871
I won’t deny myself
that pleasure any longer.

04:05.954 --> 04:07.374
Life’s too short.

04:07.456 --> 04:08.826
- But Christ said

04:08.915 --> 04:12.245
that to deny oneself
is the beginning of life.

04:12.335 --> 04:14.045
Don’t you see, Charlie?

04:14.129 --> 04:17.589
All your self-indulgence
has been so risky.

04:17.674 --> 04:20.304
Every dead Chucky
brings you one step closer

04:20.385 --> 04:22.345
to extinction.

04:22.429 --> 04:24.679
- I don’t have
to answer to you.

04:24.765 --> 04:27.735
I’m not
eight-year-old Charlie anymore,

04:27.809 --> 04:31.399
and you’re no longer
my therapist.

04:32.814 --> 04:36.074
They were weak.

04:36.151 --> 04:38.651
I was strong.

04:38.737 --> 04:41.657
I am all the Chucky

04:41.740 --> 04:45.160
anybody ever needs.

04:47.287 --> 04:49.457
Now take me to the school

04:49.539 --> 04:51.459
and let me finish this.

04:51.541 --> 04:56.421
♪ ♪

04:56.505 --> 04:58.175
- What about Andy?

04:59.758 --> 05:00.878
- [slurps]

05:00.967 --> 05:03.297
Let’s save him for dessert.

05:03.386 --> 05:05.596
♪ ♪

05:05.680 --> 05:08.350
We’ll be back soon, Andy.

05:08.433 --> 05:11.193
If you get hungry
while we’re gone,

05:11.269 --> 05:13.479
may I recommend your leg?

05:13.563 --> 05:15.113
It’s delicious.

05:19.486 --> 05:22.986
[door clicks]

05:23.073 --> 05:30.003
♪ ♪

05:53.144 --> 05:54.814
- Hey, Andy.

05:54.896 --> 05:56.556
It’s Devon and Lexy.

05:56.648 --> 05:58.438
We’re gonna untie you now.

05:58.525 --> 05:59.865
Okay?

06:05.198 --> 06:10.078
♪ ♪

06:10.161 --> 06:11.371
[dramatic musical sting]

06:11.454 --> 06:13.664
- Hey, hey,
we’re just trying to help.

06:22.716 --> 06:29.636
♪ ♪

06:36.229 --> 06:39.729
- [grunts]
- Hey, hey, hey!

06:39.816 --> 06:42.316
- It’s me, Devon.

06:42.402 --> 06:44.202
Don’t you remember?

06:44.279 --> 06:45.659
We met in Hackensack.

06:47.699 --> 06:51.329
- [grunting]

06:51.411 --> 06:52.831
- Hey.

06:52.913 --> 06:54.623
Hey.

06:54.706 --> 06:57.416
At Charles Lee Ray’s house...

06:57.500 --> 06:59.920
before it blew up.

07:00.003 --> 07:01.713
- Kyle?

07:01.796 --> 07:03.166
- Yeah.

07:03.256 --> 07:05.756
- [crying]

07:05.842 --> 07:09.392
- Hey, we’re gonna get you
out of here, okay?

07:09.471 --> 07:13.351
- We’re gonna take you
to a safe place.

07:13.433 --> 07:17.023
A different place.
With a shower.

07:17.103 --> 07:20.023
- [panting]

07:22.317 --> 07:23.607
Where is he?

07:23.693 --> 07:24.943
- Chucky’s gone.

07:25.028 --> 07:26.358
Mixter’s taking him
back to the school.

07:29.741 --> 07:30.871
Hey.

07:32.285 --> 07:34.445
- Take me there.

07:34.537 --> 07:37.417
[playful spooky music]

07:37.499 --> 07:44.379
♪ ♪

07:50.887 --> 07:53.847
[bell tolling]

07:53.932 --> 07:56.852
[eerie music]

07:56.935 --> 08:03.735
♪ ♪

08:10.365 --> 08:12.705
- Communion wafers aren’t
actually for snacking.

08:12.784 --> 08:18.214
- Careful, or you’ll wind up
like Father O’Malley--

08:18.289 --> 08:20.879
in the confessional.

08:20.959 --> 08:24.799
- Forgive me, Lord,
for questioning your works.

08:24.879 --> 08:28.879
But why did you send
Father O’Malley to his maker?

08:28.967 --> 08:32.007
- I needed to get in
a quick workout.

08:32.095 --> 08:39.025
♪ ♪

08:40.562 --> 08:42.732
Is your hair different?

08:42.814 --> 08:45.614
- Do you like it?

08:45.692 --> 08:49.902
- You know,
you should be a blonde.

08:49.988 --> 08:53.158
♪ ♪

08:53.241 --> 08:57.661
[shoes squeaking]

08:59.831 --> 09:02.671
[sighs]

09:04.210 --> 09:06.590
- I humble myself before you.

09:09.090 --> 09:11.430
[plastic squeaking]]

09:11.509 --> 09:14.639
- [chuckles]
You sure do.

09:14.721 --> 09:16.761
- Anything you wish,
simply ask,

09:16.848 --> 09:19.678
and it shall be done.

09:19.768 --> 09:22.558
- I like your style,
"Sister Act."

09:22.645 --> 09:24.305
- Sister Ruth.

09:24.397 --> 09:26.607
- Uh-huh.

09:26.691 --> 09:30.071
[car door thuds]
[car alarm beeps]

09:30.153 --> 09:33.573
♪ ♪

09:33.656 --> 09:35.906
Oh, shit.

09:35.992 --> 09:38.742
The Colonel’s here.

09:38.828 --> 09:40.708
- You told me

09:40.789 --> 09:45.039
that that Neanderthal was dead.

09:45.126 --> 09:46.876
- He was.

09:46.961 --> 09:51.011
But Charlie, you do have
a talent for resurrection.

09:51.091 --> 09:52.591
- Traitors.
- Hi!

09:52.675 --> 09:54.545
- Add them both to my list.

09:54.636 --> 09:58.176
- Please, remember you have
to make the kids’ deaths

09:58.264 --> 10:01.274
look like accidents
or suicides.

10:03.186 --> 10:05.606
- I can work with that.

10:05.688 --> 10:12.608
♪ ♪

10:16.783 --> 10:19.703
[students whispering]

10:25.208 --> 10:27.078
- [whispering]
Where’d they go?

10:27.168 --> 10:28.748
Devon didn’t come back
to the room last night.

10:28.837 --> 10:30.417
- Lexy didn’t either.

10:30.505 --> 10:33.345
Maybe they got in trouble
with Father Bryce?

10:33.424 --> 10:36.394
His punishments can be
draconian at times.

10:39.264 --> 10:42.644
[tense organ music]

10:42.725 --> 10:45.385
- As servants of the Lord,
we abide by the law of God.

10:47.730 --> 10:51.900
As members of society,
we abide by the law of man.

10:53.903 --> 10:55.403
And as students of this school,

10:55.488 --> 10:58.948
we abide by the rules
of Incarnate Lord.

11:02.036 --> 11:04.706
Now, recently,
several students think

11:04.789 --> 11:07.459
those rules are
just a suggestion.

11:07.542 --> 11:09.462
They are not.

11:09.544 --> 11:11.844
Those rules are in place
to protect us,

11:11.921 --> 11:13.591
and if they are flouted,

11:13.673 --> 11:18.053
they put each and every
single one of us in jeopardy.

11:18.136 --> 11:21.506
Now, as you know,
one of the cardinal rules here

11:21.598 --> 11:24.348
is that no student leaves
campus without permission.

11:24.434 --> 11:25.984
- Do you think they took off?

11:26.060 --> 11:27.600
- I hope not.

11:27.687 --> 11:29.647
That’s where
the draconian measures come in.

11:29.731 --> 11:36.741
♪ ♪

11:36.821 --> 11:38.361
- This rule has been broken.

11:40.283 --> 11:43.833
I have no choice but to lock
the entire school down.

11:43.912 --> 11:46.462
No extracurricular activities,
no field trips,

11:46.539 --> 11:49.039
no outdoor privileges.

11:49.125 --> 11:50.705
Every student
will remain in their room

11:50.793 --> 11:52.463
until further notice.

11:52.545 --> 11:54.085
Lockdown begins now.

11:54.172 --> 11:56.302
[students murmuring]

11:56.382 --> 11:58.302
Now!

11:58.384 --> 11:59.844
[students murmuring]

11:59.928 --> 12:01.508
- [sighs]

12:01.596 --> 12:08.476
♪ ♪

12:21.950 --> 12:24.660
- You’re not going
to get away with this.

12:24.744 --> 12:26.334
- What?
- Trevor wouldn’t run away.

12:26.412 --> 12:27.912
He’s not that stupid.

12:27.997 --> 12:31.077
Your psycho friends have him
somewhere, don’t they?

12:31.167 --> 12:33.377
- I don’t know
what you’re talking about.

12:33.461 --> 12:36.511
- What have you done to Trevor,
you fucking freak?

12:36.589 --> 12:39.429
- One more word out of you,
Ms. Del Gado,

12:39.509 --> 12:41.139
I’ll have no choice
but to recommend

12:41.219 --> 12:42.429
a transfer to juvie,

12:42.512 --> 12:44.312
where you belong.

12:44.389 --> 12:46.599
Now go to your room.

12:46.683 --> 12:49.813
[tense music]

12:49.894 --> 12:52.614
- Where’d you get that?

12:52.689 --> 12:54.649
- That’s none of your business,
Mr. Wheeler.

12:59.112 --> 13:00.652
- Mr. Wheeler,

13:00.738 --> 13:02.448
get upstairs now.

13:04.242 --> 13:06.122
- You know, don’t you?

13:06.202 --> 13:07.952
You know what he is.

13:08.037 --> 13:09.747
- I said "now."

13:09.831 --> 13:15.801
♪ ♪

13:15.878 --> 13:17.838
Dr. Mixter, I don’t know
if bringing those kids here

13:17.922 --> 13:19.882
was the best idea you ever had.

13:19.966 --> 13:22.586
- Trust me. It was.

13:22.677 --> 13:24.007
You’ll see.

13:24.095 --> 13:28.065
♪ ♪

13:28.141 --> 13:30.771
- Where did you get that?

13:30.852 --> 13:33.942
I told Sister Ruth to throw
that abomination away.

13:34.022 --> 13:37.112
- I find it’s a value
in my sessions.

13:37.191 --> 13:40.991
I use it to symbolize
my patients’ trauma.

13:41.070 --> 13:42.200
- Okay.

13:44.073 --> 13:46.583
But what happened to his hair?

13:46.659 --> 13:49.039
- [whispering]
I can’t share that with you.

13:49.120 --> 13:52.290
Doctor-patient privilege.

13:52.373 --> 13:53.753
- It doesn’t scare
the children?

13:53.833 --> 13:57.673
- Only those who already have
evil in their hearts.

13:57.754 --> 13:59.804
If you will excuse me.

13:59.881 --> 14:06.801
♪ ♪

14:35.291 --> 14:37.791
- Father, please.
Think about what you’re doing.

14:37.877 --> 14:40.667
This isn’t a prison.
Is this even legal?

14:40.755 --> 14:43.345
- The state of New Jersey
and the Archdiocese of Camden

14:43.424 --> 14:45.344
have granted me full authority
to discipline these kids

14:45.426 --> 14:46.716
as I see fit.

14:46.803 --> 14:48.803
- What do you think
that will accomplish?

14:48.888 --> 14:51.178
- As it clearly states
in Proverbs,

14:51.265 --> 14:53.845
"Whoever spares the rod
hates their children.

14:53.935 --> 14:55.695
"But the one
that loves their children

14:55.770 --> 14:57.310
are careful
to discipline them."

14:57.397 --> 14:58.557
- You’re saying
I hate these children?

14:58.648 --> 15:00.568
That’s insulting and absurd.

15:00.650 --> 15:03.940
- I’m simply quoting scripture,
Sister.

15:04.028 --> 15:06.358
- There’s nothing simple
about it.

15:06.447 --> 15:08.157
[door creaks]

15:08.241 --> 15:11.121
[reverent choral music]

15:11.202 --> 15:15.372
♪ ♪

15:15.456 --> 15:16.866
- Welcome back.

15:16.958 --> 15:17.828
- Who is this?

15:20.253 --> 15:21.343
- He’s the reason we came back.

15:23.714 --> 15:25.514
- You taught us
about Christian charity.

15:25.591 --> 15:29.471
And when we met him,
I thought to myself,

15:29.554 --> 15:32.184
"What would
Sister Catherine do?"

15:32.265 --> 15:34.435
It was clear
what we needed to do next.

15:34.517 --> 15:36.937
- I hope I’m not
getting them in trouble.

15:37.019 --> 15:39.059
They’ve been very kind to me.

15:44.193 --> 15:45.653
- How can we help you, sir?

15:47.655 --> 15:50.655
- Well, this last year’s
been really rough.

15:50.741 --> 15:55.291
Just when I’d given up hope,
these two angels found me.

15:55.371 --> 15:57.921
They told me about your church.

15:57.999 --> 15:59.749
They were sure you’d show me
some kindness.

15:59.834 --> 16:01.924
I could really use
a shower and a hot meal.

16:04.005 --> 16:05.305
- And a toothbrush.

16:06.716 --> 16:07.966
- I won’t be any trouble.

16:08.050 --> 16:10.220
I promise.

16:10.303 --> 16:11.553
- They did the right thing.

16:11.637 --> 16:13.807
The church is always here
for people in need.

16:13.890 --> 16:16.770
[tense music]

16:16.851 --> 16:19.561
♪ ♪

16:19.645 --> 16:20.845
- Sister,
we don’t know this man.

16:20.938 --> 16:22.148
The school is on lockdown,

16:22.231 --> 16:23.821
and I find it
wholly inappropriate

16:23.900 --> 16:26.110
to bring a stranger,
right now, into our midst.

16:26.194 --> 16:28.204
- "Contribute to the needs
of God’s people,

16:28.279 --> 16:29.949
and welcome strangers
into your home."

16:30.031 --> 16:31.451
Romans 12:13.

16:31.532 --> 16:33.202
Or does the word of God
only count

16:33.284 --> 16:34.744
when it’s coming
from your mouth, Father?

16:34.827 --> 16:37.707
- I don’t think that applies
to these circumstances.

16:37.788 --> 16:38.868
- Why not?

16:38.956 --> 16:41.746
Isn’t it commanded
in the Bible?

16:41.834 --> 16:43.254
What’s your name, sir?

16:43.336 --> 16:44.706
- It’s Andy.

16:44.795 --> 16:46.835
- Come with me, Andy.
Let’s get you cleaned up.

16:46.923 --> 16:49.513
- Thank you, Sister.

16:49.592 --> 16:52.222
- I would like to see him
in my office after.

16:52.303 --> 16:54.013
- Will do.
- Thank you, Sister.

16:57.183 --> 16:59.313
Upstairs.

16:59.393 --> 17:02.063
I’ll be there in a minute
to lock you in.

17:02.146 --> 17:04.856
No detours, no shenanigans.
You understand?

17:04.941 --> 17:06.401
- Got it.

17:06.484 --> 17:08.744
- Shenanigan-free.

17:08.819 --> 17:15.739
♪ ♪

17:17.870 --> 17:19.960
[lock clicks]

17:23.668 --> 17:26.088
- No detours, no shenanigans.

17:26.170 --> 17:28.670
- Perfect example
of the idiot patriarchy.

17:28.756 --> 17:32.426
- Look who’s back.

17:32.510 --> 17:34.930
You know leaving campus
violates your court order.

17:35.012 --> 17:38.892
I could have you thrown
out of here if I wanted to.

17:38.975 --> 17:40.735
But that’s not what I want,

17:40.810 --> 17:44.440
nor what he wants.

17:44.522 --> 17:47.482
He wants you here

17:47.567 --> 17:49.567
where he can get you.

17:49.652 --> 17:53.032
[suspenseful music]

17:53.114 --> 17:54.324
- So how does it feel

17:54.407 --> 17:56.697
being a red-headed doll’s
little bitch?

17:56.784 --> 17:59.584
- Word of advice:

17:59.662 --> 18:04.122
do not mention hair
to the Colonel.

18:04.208 --> 18:08.088
♪ ♪

18:08.170 --> 18:09.880
- You’re gonna pay
for what you did to Andy.

18:09.964 --> 18:11.884
- Who would believe you?

18:14.927 --> 18:17.297
He’s going to kill

18:17.388 --> 18:19.178
each and every one of you,

18:19.265 --> 18:22.435
and I am absolutely
going to watch.

18:22.518 --> 18:24.688
♪ ♪

18:28.441 --> 18:29.981
- [screams]

18:30.610 --> 18:32.490
[intense music]

18:32.570 --> 18:36.620
[screaming]

18:36.699 --> 18:38.119
- [gasps]

18:38.200 --> 18:41.040
[panting]

18:41.120 --> 18:44.000
[soft dramatic music]

18:44.081 --> 18:51.001
♪ ♪

18:55.217 --> 18:56.717
[text whooshes]

18:59.555 --> 19:03.175
[phone dinging]

19:22.244 --> 19:25.164
[indistinct news broadcast]

19:28.751 --> 19:30.381
- Is that really necessary?

19:32.797 --> 19:35.917
- Well, he’s still inside her,
and you’re still his kid.

19:36.008 --> 19:38.758
So yeah, it’s necessary.

19:45.976 --> 19:48.436
Now can you tell us what’s
gonna happen when we get there?

19:48.521 --> 19:50.771
- Chucky just said
there will be somebody there

19:50.856 --> 19:52.606
who will help set us both free.

19:52.692 --> 19:54.742
- And we’re just supposed
to take his word for it?

19:54.819 --> 19:57.569
- He wants out
as much as I want him out.

19:57.655 --> 20:00.245
Trust me.

20:00.324 --> 20:02.084
- How do you talk to him
in there?

20:05.996 --> 20:09.076
- It’s kind of hard to explain.

20:09.166 --> 20:11.076
- Does he ever mention Andy?

20:15.297 --> 20:18.797
- You think he’s still alive?
- I know he is.

20:18.884 --> 20:21.054
They never found his body.

20:21.137 --> 20:23.637
That’s why I went to LA
in the first place.

20:23.723 --> 20:25.723
I thought maybe
your maniac mother took him.

20:25.808 --> 20:26.978
- [scoffs]

20:29.979 --> 20:32.269
- I really hope you find him.

20:32.356 --> 20:33.816
- Thank you.

20:36.318 --> 20:38.278
- They really have taken
almost everything from us,

20:38.362 --> 20:40.112
haven’t they?

20:40.197 --> 20:45.947
♪ ♪

20:47.830 --> 20:48.830
- Almost.

20:53.836 --> 20:55.626
Listen, I really hate
to ask this of you,

20:55.713 --> 20:58.473
but, um...

20:58.549 --> 20:59.469
- What?

21:01.343 --> 21:03.803
You wanna talk to him,
don’t you?

21:03.888 --> 21:05.638
- Sorry.

21:09.477 --> 21:10.437
- Yeah.

21:12.480 --> 21:14.150
Yeah.

21:15.983 --> 21:17.323
[exhales]

21:17.401 --> 21:18.821
- You ready?

21:18.903 --> 21:20.863
- No, but do it.

21:20.946 --> 21:23.816
[suspenseful music]

21:23.908 --> 21:30.828
♪ ♪

21:32.541 --> 21:35.501
- [grunting]

21:40.090 --> 21:42.340
[chuckles]
Glenda.

21:45.721 --> 21:47.511
Oh, you’re still alive?

21:47.598 --> 21:49.138
- Surprise, fucker.

21:49.225 --> 21:51.735
- But the whole house exploded.

21:51.811 --> 21:54.521
You’re telling me not one
person died in that explosion?

21:54.605 --> 21:55.865
- Just shut up and listen.
- [laughing]

21:55.940 --> 21:57.520
- We’re gonna be
in Jersey tonight,

21:57.608 --> 21:59.858
and I’ll help you and Nica
go your separate ways,

21:59.944 --> 22:03.704
but you have to tell me
where Andy is!

22:03.781 --> 22:06.071
- Oh, Andy Barclay?

22:06.158 --> 22:08.408
I killed him.

22:08.494 --> 22:10.704
He cried like a little bitch
when I cut out his tongue,

22:10.788 --> 22:11.908
like this.

22:11.997 --> 22:14.077
[mimics retching]

22:14.166 --> 22:17.086
[cackling]

22:19.046 --> 22:20.206
- Bullshit.

22:22.424 --> 22:25.684
- Shitface, I’m sick of looking
at this bitch already.

22:25.761 --> 22:27.051
Kill her for me, will ya?

22:27.137 --> 22:29.217
- She has the gun.

22:31.392 --> 22:35.022
- Oh, there you go, Shitface.

22:35.104 --> 22:36.234
[suspenseful music]

22:36.313 --> 22:39.403
Do it.

22:39.483 --> 22:41.533
Glenda, do it.

22:42.736 --> 22:43.696
Glenda!

22:45.489 --> 22:46.909
- Turn him back.

22:46.991 --> 22:48.621
- What,
are you fucking kidding me?

22:48.701 --> 22:50.291
It’s not like
you haven’t done it before!

22:50.369 --> 22:51.539
- Would you turn him back?

22:51.620 --> 22:53.620
- Glenda--

22:53.706 --> 22:57.416
- [groaning]

22:59.503 --> 23:01.633
Does it have to be that hard?

23:01.714 --> 23:04.634
- Los Angeles
for some breaking news.

23:04.717 --> 23:06.297
- Authorities
continue their search

23:06.385 --> 23:08.215
for actress Jennifer Tilly,

23:08.304 --> 23:10.434
wanted for questioning--
- Holy shit.

23:10.514 --> 23:12.104
- In connection
with multiple homicides

23:13.767 --> 23:15.477
at her Beverly Hills home,
which was destroyed by fire

23:15.561 --> 23:16.901
just days ago.

23:16.979 --> 23:18.979
Reportedly, among the deceased

23:19.064 --> 23:21.944
are beloved character actors
Joe Pantoliano

23:22.026 --> 23:24.816
and Meg Tilly,
the Oscar-nominated sister

23:24.904 --> 23:27.954
of Jennifer,
herself an Oscar nominee.

23:28.032 --> 23:30.832
Tilly’s two children are
also wanted for questioning.

23:30.910 --> 23:33.580
A manhunt is underway.

23:33.662 --> 23:35.412
Next up in sports.

23:35.497 --> 23:38.457
- With the big football game
on--

23:38.542 --> 23:40.792
- Looks like
we’re both fugitives now.

23:44.465 --> 23:47.475
[fly buzzing]

23:55.601 --> 23:57.981
- So they were eating him?

23:58.062 --> 23:59.692
- Yep.

23:59.772 --> 24:01.612
Something I never get to unsee.

24:01.690 --> 24:02.860
- Jesus.

24:04.860 --> 24:08.200
Man, I can’t believe you
and Lexy just went out there.

24:08.280 --> 24:10.370
You know, alone at night.

24:13.160 --> 24:16.160
- And now we have this Colonel
asshole to deal with.

24:16.246 --> 24:18.036
He’s bad, Jake.

24:18.123 --> 24:20.003
Maybe the worst we’ve seen yet.

24:20.084 --> 24:22.294
- I mean, we’ve taken care
of Chuckys before,

24:22.378 --> 24:25.378
but now we have Mixter
to deal with.

24:25.464 --> 24:27.174
You know, and she could
just call us in for therapy

24:27.257 --> 24:30.177
whenever she wants.

24:30.260 --> 24:32.220
- [sighs]

24:32.304 --> 24:34.064
It’s dark.

24:34.139 --> 24:36.389
Super, super dark.

24:36.475 --> 24:39.185
[eerie music]

24:39.269 --> 24:41.349
- Then maybe we need
to get light.

24:41.438 --> 24:43.358
- [sighs] Jake, if this is some

24:43.440 --> 24:45.480
"light of the Lord"
post-baptism shit you’re on,

24:45.567 --> 24:47.027
I’m really not in the mood.

24:47.111 --> 24:49.361
- Wait, no, I mean,
like, light,

24:49.446 --> 24:51.236
like, as in nimble.

24:51.323 --> 24:52.913
You know, agile.

24:52.992 --> 24:54.582
Ready for anything.

24:54.660 --> 24:56.750
You know, whatever battle
this Colonel has brewing,

24:56.829 --> 24:59.159
we need to have it
on our own terms.

24:59.248 --> 25:01.578
- And what terms
would those be?

25:01.667 --> 25:02.827
- Home court advantage.

25:02.918 --> 25:04.208
- I’m sorry.

25:04.294 --> 25:06.554
You’re referring
to this horror show as home?

25:06.630 --> 25:09.670
- Well, I mean,
this room is our turf.

25:09.758 --> 25:12.588
You know, we can control
what happens here.

25:12.678 --> 25:15.008
- Have Chucky come to us.

25:15.097 --> 25:16.177
When have I heard that before?

25:16.265 --> 25:18.395
- [sighs]
Well, I mean,

25:18.475 --> 25:20.885
not just come to us.

25:20.978 --> 25:22.518
No, to all of us.

25:22.604 --> 25:25.574
Look, all of us
in one room, ready.

25:25.649 --> 25:29.899
Look, you, me, Lexy, Nadine,
and Good Chucky.

25:29.987 --> 25:32.907
[fly buzzing]

25:34.324 --> 25:36.244
- You really, really, really

25:36.326 --> 25:38.076
want this Good Chucky thing
to work out.

25:38.162 --> 25:41.082
- Well, I mean, it already has
worked for us, Devon.

25:41.165 --> 25:43.545
I mean, you saw what he did
to that other Chucky.

25:46.420 --> 25:49.210
- He is good at killing
other Chuckys.

25:51.842 --> 25:53.222
- Hey, you know...

25:56.305 --> 25:58.435
It was brave.

25:58.515 --> 25:59.925
You know,
what you and Lexy did.

26:00.017 --> 26:02.937
[soft music]

26:03.020 --> 26:06.940
♪ ♪

26:07.024 --> 26:09.904
[fly buzzing]

26:12.654 --> 26:14.074
- Hmm?

26:14.156 --> 26:16.986
[suspenseful music]

26:17.076 --> 26:21.116
♪ ♪

26:21.205 --> 26:22.585
[fly squishes]

26:26.210 --> 26:29.170
[Just Mustard’s "Seven"]

26:29.254 --> 26:32.134
[dark rock music]

26:32.216 --> 26:35.676
♪ ♪

26:35.761 --> 26:37.641
- You didn’t throw up.

26:37.721 --> 26:40.311
- The night is young.

26:40.390 --> 26:42.600
- ♪ Bless me ♪

26:42.684 --> 26:46.614
- [breathing heavily]

26:46.688 --> 26:51.938
- ♪ There’s a ghost again ♪

26:52.027 --> 26:55.657
♪ In the shed ♪
- [groans]

26:55.739 --> 26:59.329
♪ ♪

26:59.409 --> 27:05.619
- ♪ I can’t see ♪

27:05.707 --> 27:07.827
♪ This make-believe ♪

27:07.918 --> 27:10.998
- [breathing heavily]

27:11.088 --> 27:15.838
- ♪ Does my head in ♪

27:15.926 --> 27:18.676
[water pouring]

27:18.762 --> 27:25.692
♪ ♪

27:49.293 --> 27:50.383
[knock at door]

27:50.460 --> 27:51.710
- Come in.

27:51.795 --> 27:54.545
[door creaks]
- It’s me.

27:54.631 --> 27:58.091
It’s Sister Ruth.

27:58.177 --> 27:59.427
- What is it?

28:02.472 --> 28:05.392
- Father, as you know,
I am and have always been

28:05.475 --> 28:07.555
His most humble servant.

28:08.979 --> 28:11.109
- I don’t have time
to give out gold stars

28:11.190 --> 28:13.400
for His most humble servant
right now, Sister.

28:13.483 --> 28:15.573
- This is not piety.

28:15.652 --> 28:17.782
This is--

28:17.863 --> 28:21.573
well, I believe
this is a miracle.

28:21.658 --> 28:24.578
[eerie music]

28:24.661 --> 28:29.251
♪ ♪

28:29.333 --> 28:32.423
He has risen.

28:32.502 --> 28:38.432
♪ ♪

28:38.508 --> 28:40.048
- Did you get that
from Dr. Mixter?

28:40.135 --> 28:41.755
- What?

28:41.845 --> 28:44.215
No.

28:44.306 --> 28:46.556
- So many dolls, Sister.

28:48.310 --> 28:50.600
I told you to throw
this monstrosity out yesterday,

28:50.687 --> 28:52.477
but here it is.

28:52.564 --> 28:55.904
Same doll, sitting on my desk,

28:55.984 --> 28:57.244
reeking of garbage.
- I did.

28:57.319 --> 28:59.739
Father, I did throw him out.

29:01.156 --> 29:02.736
- It.

29:02.824 --> 29:06.244
- Yes,
I threw it in the trash can

29:06.328 --> 29:09.118
as you instructed me to,
but then when I returned,

29:09.206 --> 29:11.746
he was--sorry, it.

29:11.833 --> 29:13.963
Well, I found it, and--

29:14.044 --> 29:15.174
- Spit it out.

29:15.254 --> 29:19.304
He is our Lord and Savior.

29:19.383 --> 29:25.973
♪ ♪

29:38.902 --> 29:40.652
- Let us pray, Sister,

29:40.737 --> 29:43.617
so that this--this frenzy,

29:43.699 --> 29:48.329
this--this fever
that has overtaken you

29:48.412 --> 29:51.832
shall pass from you

29:51.915 --> 29:53.165
to me...

29:56.003 --> 29:57.633
With the strength
of the prayer.

29:57.713 --> 30:00.173
And then it,

30:00.257 --> 30:03.177
with our Lord’s blessing,

30:03.260 --> 30:06.470
it shall be gone.

30:06.555 --> 30:09.565
- Our Lord
is sitting right there.

30:09.641 --> 30:11.851
It is no fever.

30:16.273 --> 30:18.733
- This school is on lockdown.

30:18.817 --> 30:21.357
That means everybody
is confined to their room,

30:21.445 --> 30:23.205
including you.

30:23.280 --> 30:25.200
Doubly so
in the light of this heresy.

30:25.282 --> 30:27.332
- Stop dismissing me!

30:27.409 --> 30:30.909
This is real.
He has risen!

30:30.996 --> 30:34.036
- Sister, go to your room.

30:37.586 --> 30:39.206
- Yes, Father Bryce.

30:44.593 --> 30:45.893
Right away.

30:45.969 --> 30:52.849
♪ ♪

31:08.742 --> 31:11.622
[suspenseful music]

31:11.703 --> 31:14.213
♪ ♪

31:14.289 --> 31:17.079
- Nice seeing you
out and about, baldy.

31:17.167 --> 31:20.207
What’s the occasion, wig sale?

31:20.295 --> 31:22.415
[cackles]

31:22.506 --> 31:24.756
[munches]

31:24.841 --> 31:26.591
- Stand down, soldier.

31:26.676 --> 31:29.886
You think that because
you put on a little muscle,

31:29.971 --> 31:32.431
you can defy me?

31:32.516 --> 31:36.096
- That’s exactly what I think.

31:37.479 --> 31:38.979
- Be careful.

31:39.064 --> 31:43.114
Thinking isn’t
your strong suit.

31:43.193 --> 31:45.903
- Huh.

31:45.987 --> 31:47.657
All right, cue ball.

31:47.739 --> 31:51.279
Time to get this over with.

31:51.368 --> 31:53.618
[crunches]

31:53.703 --> 31:58.333
- Correction, soldier.
It’s already over.

31:58.417 --> 31:59.917
- [choking]

32:00.001 --> 32:03.461
- Arsenic.
Special family recipe.

32:05.382 --> 32:07.802
- [sniffs]

32:07.884 --> 32:10.514
- Mind over muscle every time.

32:10.595 --> 32:12.675
- [choking]

32:12.764 --> 32:15.854
- General George S. Patton
said,

32:15.934 --> 32:19.274
"It is foolish"...
- [choking]

32:19.354 --> 32:21.694
- "To mourn those
who have died.

32:21.773 --> 32:26.283
"Rather, we should thank God

32:26.361 --> 32:30.161
that such men existed."

32:30.240 --> 32:33.370
- [choking]

32:36.663 --> 32:39.873
- So thank you, God, because...

32:39.958 --> 32:43.338
[laughing] That was
the fucking funniest thing

32:43.420 --> 32:45.340
I’ve seen all year.

32:45.422 --> 32:48.342
[laughing]

32:48.425 --> 32:50.515
♪ ♪

32:55.474 --> 32:58.484
[tense music]

32:58.935 --> 32:59.685
♪ ♪

32:59.769 --> 33:02.689
[both grunting]

33:07.319 --> 33:08.319
- Ow.

33:08.403 --> 33:10.703
- Impressive.

33:10.780 --> 33:12.700
- Please, I didn’t do shit.

33:12.782 --> 33:15.872
Nadine practically carried me
the whole way up.

33:15.952 --> 33:19.332
- Krav Maga really is
a total body workout.

33:19.414 --> 33:21.544
- Glad you guys could make it.

33:21.625 --> 33:23.885
- So what’s the latest intel?

33:23.960 --> 33:25.290
- According to Andy,

33:25.378 --> 33:26.878
the Colonel’s
the last doll standing.

33:26.963 --> 33:29.803
Well,
the last evil one, anyway.

33:29.883 --> 33:32.143
- Well, that’s kind of
good news, right?

33:32.219 --> 33:34.549
Weren’t there
a lot of bad Chuckys?

33:34.638 --> 33:36.848
- There were, out in the woods.

33:39.601 --> 33:42.691
- But...
- The Colonel went apeshit.

33:42.771 --> 33:44.401
I mean, he killed
all the other Chuckys,

33:44.481 --> 33:46.071
his own men.

33:46.149 --> 33:50.069
He’s vicious,
and now he’s gonna come for us.

33:50.153 --> 33:53.573
♪ ♪

33:53.657 --> 33:54.907
- Wait. Hey, Lexy, Lexy.

33:54.991 --> 33:56.531
What are you doing?

33:56.618 --> 33:58.238
- Move, please.

33:58.328 --> 33:59.578
- It’s five against two.

34:01.456 --> 34:02.826
- I’m not following.

34:02.916 --> 34:05.416
- Six, actually. Andy’s coming.

34:05.502 --> 34:08.502
- Yeah,
he seemed super reliable.

34:08.588 --> 34:10.378
- Don’t you want this
to be over?

34:10.465 --> 34:11.755
- Yes, Jake,

34:11.841 --> 34:13.261
I very much want this
to be over,

34:13.343 --> 34:15.853
which is why I wanna barricade
the fucking door.

34:15.929 --> 34:18.889
- This is how we win.

34:18.974 --> 34:20.434
Look,
when he comes through the door,

34:20.517 --> 34:22.057
we’ll be here,

34:22.143 --> 34:24.273
and we’ll be more ready
than we’ve ever been.

34:24.354 --> 34:27.364
♪ ♪

34:27.440 --> 34:30.280
Hey, do you have the stuff?

34:30.360 --> 34:31.570
- Boy, do I ever.

34:31.653 --> 34:35.573
♪ ♪

34:35.657 --> 34:37.617
Okay.

34:37.701 --> 34:41.251
We can stab,

34:41.329 --> 34:42.749
poison,

34:42.831 --> 34:45.421
bludgeon,

34:45.500 --> 34:47.040
concuss,

34:47.127 --> 34:50.127
and, for my sweet baby boy,

34:50.213 --> 34:53.053
we’ve got good old-fashioned
hand-to-hand combat,

34:53.133 --> 34:54.633
so you can be just like me.

34:54.718 --> 34:56.048
- Oh, wow.

34:58.847 --> 35:00.807
- This is insane.

35:06.354 --> 35:07.984
- Nadine, we’re not babysitting
here, you know?

35:08.064 --> 35:09.984
- [sighs]
- Sure we are.

35:10.066 --> 35:13.986
Good Chucky is the baby,
and you and Jake are the dads.

35:14.070 --> 35:17.280
- I think I’m gonna throw up.

35:17.365 --> 35:19.155
- What, do you not
wanna have kids?

35:19.242 --> 35:23.082
- Lexy,
you look a little nervous.

35:23.163 --> 35:24.333
- I just don’t think
we’re responsible...

35:24.414 --> 35:26.504
- Want something
to help with that?

35:26.583 --> 35:28.333
- And besides, we’re, like, 16.

35:28.418 --> 35:29.958
[suspenseful music]

35:30.045 --> 35:32.425
- Not now.
Like, in the future.

35:32.505 --> 35:34.415
[coins rattling]

35:34.507 --> 35:35.797
- Well, if you ask me,

35:35.884 --> 35:37.094
I think you guys are gonna be
great dads.

35:37.177 --> 35:38.847
- Thanks.

35:38.928 --> 35:42.348
[knife scraping]

35:42.432 --> 35:49.362
♪ ♪

35:56.905 --> 35:59.875
[door creaks]

36:02.827 --> 36:05.707
[distorted trumpet music]

36:05.789 --> 36:08.539
♪ ♪

36:08.625 --> 36:12.505
- Give me liberty,

36:12.587 --> 36:15.337
or give me death.

36:15.423 --> 36:19.143
♪ ♪

36:19.219 --> 36:23.059
Remember the Alamo!

36:23.139 --> 36:27.229
♪ ♪

36:27.310 --> 36:32.190
Khan...

36:38.279 --> 36:39.989
- Who’s Khan?

36:40.073 --> 36:42.833
- [breathing heavily]

36:42.909 --> 36:45.199
[grunting]

36:45.286 --> 36:46.996
- The horror.

36:48.248 --> 36:52.538
[groaning]

36:52.627 --> 36:54.087
The horror...

36:54.170 --> 36:57.050
[dark psychedelic rock music]

36:57.132 --> 36:59.092
♪ ♪

36:59.175 --> 37:01.085
[echoing]
The horror...

37:01.177 --> 37:08.097
♪ ♪

37:11.604 --> 37:13.114
The horror...

37:13.189 --> 37:15.779
♪ ♪

37:15.859 --> 37:17.739
The horror...

37:17.819 --> 37:20.359
♪ ♪

37:20.447 --> 37:22.237
- You should’ve cut deeper.

37:22.323 --> 37:25.873
- [wheezes]

37:31.958 --> 37:33.248
- [gasps]

37:33.334 --> 37:36.714
Hey, don’t I know you
from somewhere?

37:38.173 --> 37:39.803
- What the fuck is this?

37:39.883 --> 37:42.803
[dramatic music]

37:42.886 --> 37:44.426
♪ ♪

37:44.512 --> 37:47.432
- [whimpering]

37:47.515 --> 37:54.395
♪ ♪

37:59.527 --> 38:00.947
[shoe squeaks]

38:01.029 --> 38:06.909
♪ ♪

38:06.993 --> 38:08.743
I will avenge thee,

38:08.828 --> 38:09.998
my Lord.

38:10.079 --> 38:16.999
♪ ♪

38:18.671 --> 38:21.671
[sobbing]

38:23.718 --> 38:26.678
[phone vibrating]

38:28.389 --> 38:29.969
- Hello, Charlie.

38:30.058 --> 38:31.348
- We’ll be there by midnight.

38:31.434 --> 38:32.814
- You need to hurry.

38:32.894 --> 38:35.194
There is only
one good guy doll left.

38:35.271 --> 38:36.811
- Yeah, yeah, Doc.

38:36.898 --> 38:41.108
♪ ♪

38:41.194 --> 38:43.784
Pick up the pace, kid.
We got places to be.

38:43.863 --> 38:45.033
- Righty-o, daddy-o.

38:45.114 --> 38:46.494
[engine revs]

38:46.574 --> 38:48.164
- [cackles]

38:48.243 --> 38:49.543
You know, I’m flattered, Kyle,

38:49.619 --> 38:52.119
but you’re not really
my type anymore, you know?

38:52.205 --> 38:55.675
Also, what the fuck
did you do to your hair?

38:55.750 --> 38:58.170
- Okay, I refuse to ride
another second with him.

38:58.253 --> 39:01.553
- [cackling]

39:01.631 --> 39:02.551
Ow!

39:09.389 --> 39:12.179
[suspenseful music]

39:12.642 --> 39:15.522
♪ ♪

39:15.603 --> 39:17.733
- [gasps]

39:17.814 --> 39:19.904
- Hey.
- Jake, let him go.

39:19.983 --> 39:22.233
- Look, I know
what this looks like.

39:22.318 --> 39:23.738
But he’s different, Andy.
He saved our lives.

39:23.820 --> 39:25.820
He’s good.

39:25.905 --> 39:27.735
- They all need to die.

39:27.824 --> 39:29.414
There’s no such thing
as a good Chucky.

39:29.492 --> 39:30.912
[both grunt]

39:30.994 --> 39:32.414
- Ow!
[gun cocks]

39:32.495 --> 39:35.245
- For once, Mr. Barclay,
I agree with you.

39:35.331 --> 39:37.921
♪ ♪

39:38.001 --> 39:39.501
[door slams]
- Let us out!

39:39.586 --> 39:42.246
- Who are you?
Where are you taking me?

39:42.338 --> 39:43.918
Jake needs me.
[pounding on door]

39:44.007 --> 39:46.757
- Snap out of it, Charlie.

39:46.843 --> 39:49.263
- My name is Good Chucky,
I’ll have you know.

39:49.345 --> 39:52.095
- And that is the problem.

39:52.181 --> 39:55.731
When I first met you,
when you were seven,

39:55.810 --> 39:58.100
there was a stream
of innocence in you,

39:58.187 --> 40:00.767
despite your more
interesting qualities.

40:00.857 --> 40:04.567
A naivete that wasn’t
surprising in a child,

40:04.652 --> 40:07.282
but frankly, as your therapist,
I found it boring.

40:07.363 --> 40:09.913
I did my best
to stamp it out of you.

40:09.991 --> 40:11.621
What those children have
done to you, I don’t know,

40:11.701 --> 40:15.291
but sadly--oh, Charlie,

40:15.371 --> 40:16.751
I think it’s hopeless.

40:16.831 --> 40:19.131
- What do you mean?
- Let us out, you bitch!

40:19.208 --> 40:21.538
- You’re going to have
to leave this body, Charlie,

40:21.628 --> 40:24.458
to make way
for a better part of you,

40:24.547 --> 40:26.217
the best part.

40:26.299 --> 40:27.759
- Leave my body?

40:27.842 --> 40:29.932
Where will I go?

40:30.011 --> 40:31.641
- I’m a psychiatrist,
not a theologian.

40:31.721 --> 40:33.261
That’s a question for Father...

40:33.348 --> 40:35.138
Bryce!

40:35.224 --> 40:37.774
- Help! I’m being kidnapped!

40:37.852 --> 40:39.482
- Not only do I collect dolls,

40:39.562 --> 40:41.902
I dabble
in ventriloquism as well.

40:41.981 --> 40:43.821
[chuckles]
- She’s crazy!

40:43.900 --> 40:45.480
Please help me!

40:45.568 --> 40:46.898
- That’s incredible.

40:46.986 --> 40:48.276
- How many of those things
are there?

40:48.363 --> 40:50.243
- What do you mean?
- [grunting]

40:50.323 --> 40:51.913
- I’m starting to think this
weird obsession with dolls

40:51.991 --> 40:53.281
is contagious, ’cause I had

40:53.368 --> 40:55.288
the most bizarre encounter
with Sister Ruth--

40:55.370 --> 40:56.500
[gunshot fires]

40:56.579 --> 41:00.789
♪ ♪

41:00.875 --> 41:02.285
Okay.

41:02.377 --> 41:04.837
♪ ♪

41:04.921 --> 41:08.131
- [grunting]

41:08.216 --> 41:14.846
♪ ♪

41:16.057 --> 41:17.807
[grunts]
- Andy!

41:17.892 --> 41:21.772
♪ ♪

41:21.854 --> 41:24.194
- Help!
She’s trying to kill me!

41:24.273 --> 41:26.483
- Good Chucky, wait!

41:26.567 --> 41:28.317
- Nadine, no!

41:28.403 --> 41:31.323
[both grunting]

41:31.406 --> 41:35.696
♪ ♪

41:35.785 --> 41:38.835
- [breathing heavily]

41:38.913 --> 41:41.833
Nice try, Mr. Barclay.

41:41.916 --> 41:43.496
- Good Chucky, wait!

41:46.212 --> 41:47.462
- Nadine, no!

41:49.924 --> 41:52.304
Nadine, open the door!

41:52.385 --> 41:54.145
[door knob rattling]
Nadine, open--

41:54.220 --> 41:55.470
Nadine!
- Hey!

41:55.555 --> 41:56.855
- Sister Catherine,
did you see that?

41:56.931 --> 41:58.391
- Yes.
- Nadine, open the door!

41:58.474 --> 42:00.024
- Nadine, come on,
open the door!

42:00.101 --> 42:02.231
- Where are you right now,
psychically?

42:02.311 --> 42:03.981
- Nadine, please open the door!

42:04.063 --> 42:05.523
- I think we should
call the police.

42:07.108 --> 42:09.398
- No.

42:09.485 --> 42:11.485
We need to call the Vatican.

42:11.571 --> 42:15.871
- Father Bryce,
what an interesting idea.

42:15.950 --> 42:19.250
♪ ♪

42:19.328 --> 42:20.698
- Good Chucky?

42:20.788 --> 42:23.248
Don’t be afraid.
It’s me. I’m here.

42:23.332 --> 42:24.752
- I don’t deserve you.

42:24.834 --> 42:26.884
I don’t deserve any of you.

42:26.961 --> 42:28.251
I’m bad.

42:28.337 --> 42:29.757
- No, you’re not bad.

42:29.839 --> 42:31.049
You’ve been baptized
in the Lord.

42:31.132 --> 42:32.422
It’s okay.

42:32.508 --> 42:35.548
Your godmother is here
to protect you now.

42:35.636 --> 42:37.756
- My fairy godmother?

42:37.847 --> 42:40.517
- That’s right.

42:40.600 --> 42:41.890
- [grunts]

42:41.976 --> 42:43.056
Nadine, wait!

42:45.313 --> 42:46.863
- Hey.

42:46.939 --> 42:49.779
Do you know
what fairies like to do?

42:49.859 --> 42:51.439
- What?

42:51.527 --> 42:53.067
- Nadine!

42:53.154 --> 42:56.574
♪ ♪

42:56.657 --> 42:57.617
- [screams]

42:57.700 --> 42:59.030
- Nadine!
[gasping]

42:59.118 --> 43:01.748
- They like to fly.

43:01.829 --> 43:03.959
- [screaming]

43:04.040 --> 43:05.420
[bell tolls]

43:05.500 --> 43:06.630
- Nadine!

43:06.709 --> 43:09.419
[crying]
No!

43:09.504 --> 43:10.924
No!

43:11.005 --> 43:12.415
- [snickering]

43:12.507 --> 43:14.717
Defenestration.

43:14.801 --> 43:18.101
It’s always been
my favorite MO.

43:18.179 --> 43:21.099
[snickers]

43:21.182 --> 43:23.732
♪ ♪

43:23.810 --> 43:25.310
Jake?

43:25.394 --> 43:27.274
What have I done?

43:29.649 --> 43:32.649
- [sobbing]

43:32.735 --> 43:35.605
[somber choral music]

43:35.696 --> 43:38.656
♪ ♪

43:38.741 --> 43:41.621
[bell tolls]

43:41.702 --> 43:48.632
♪ ♪
